1. Check Cluster Status
oc status

2. Get Cluster Information
oc cluster-info

3. Check Node Utilization
oc adm top nodes

21. Check Cluster Operators

oc get co
oc describe co <operator-name>
Lists the cluster operators and provides their details and status.

22. Get Cluster Version Information

oc get clusterversion
oc describe clusterversion
Displays the current OpenShift cluster version and upgrade history.

23. Check Cluster Health

oc get clusteroperator
oc describe clusteroperator <operator-name>
Provides information about the health and status of cluster operators.

24. Check OpenShift Routes

oc get route
oc describe route <route-name>
Lists routes and provides detailed information.

25. Check Build Configurations and Builds

oc get buildconfig
oc describe buildconfig <buildconfig-name>
oc get builds
oc describe build <build-name>
Displays build configuration and build status.


27. Get Projects
oc get projects

28. Switch Project
oc project <project_name>

29. Get Images
oc get images

30. Get ImageStreams
oc get is

31. Describe ImageStream
oc describe is <imagestream_name>

33. Get Running Pods
oc get pods --field-selector=status.phase=Running

34. Get Failed Pods
oc get pods --field-selector=status.phase=Failed

36. Debugging Pod Issues
oc debug pod/<pod-name>
Launches a debug container to troubleshoot issues with a pod.

37. Execute Commands Inside a Container
oc exec <pod-name> -c <container-name> -- <command>
oc exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/bash

38. Check API server logs for errors:
oc logs -n openshift-apiserver $(oc get pods -n openshift-apiserver -l apiserver=true -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')

39. Evict all pods from a node (drain a node):
oc adm drain <node_name> --force --ignore-daemonsets --delete-emptydir-data

40. Analyze audit logs for security-related issues or actions:
oc adm node-logs --role=master --path=audit

41. View OpenShift internal component logs:
oc logs -n openshift-kube-apiserver $(oc get pods -n openshift-kube-apiserver -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
oc logs -n openshift-controller-manager $(oc get pods -n openshift-controller-manager -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')

42. Performance and Resource Usage

Check top resource-consuming pods:
oc adm top pods -A
Check memory and CPU usage of nodes:
oc adm top nodes
Monitor API server metrics for performance bottlenecks:
oc adm top apiserver

43. Advanced Debugging
Use debug command to create a debug pod for troubleshooting:
oc debug node/<node_name>
oc debug pod/<pod_name> -n <namespace>

Check for security context constraints (SCCs) issues:
oc get scc
oc describe scc <scc_name>

